<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-10-31T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-10-31T19:00:00-05:00" n="74" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d74">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72119 P 43/906: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Special Representative</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_HCEM1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">House</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                                </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-11-01T00:00:00+00:00">November 1, 1918—12 a.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 1 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>28. I suggest that you discuss with the President the advisability of
                            authorizing me to use my discretion in securing options for
                            accommodations for the American representatives at the ultimate Peace
                            Conference. Of course, at the present time it has not been <pb facs="0190" n="120" xml:id="pg_120"/> definitely decided when or
                            where this Conference will take place. It may be necessary however for
                            quick action to be taken, and accordingly I would appreciate an
                            expression of your opinion concerning this matter.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_HCEM1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">House</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>